For further practical demonstration of the synthesized PbS-I NC inks, broadband photodetectors were fabricated and characterized. Figure 4a shows the schematic structure of the photodetector with a channel length and width of 20 µm and 1 mm, respectively. For a photodetector, responsivity (R) and specific detectivity (D*) are two key figures-of-merit40. R is defined as R=IphPin\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
